=m><span class=title> Haste cap</span><hr size=1> I have read and heard a million diff. opinions on the haste cap for melee characters.  What I hear most often is that pre 51 the cap is 75% and after that it goes to 105 %.  Anyone do any tests or ave any data that will help anwser this cap question?<br>
<br>
I hope it is 105% at 51+, cause with our epic and AQ, will will just hit it.  Otherwise, the haste on our epic is worthless with a 50+ enchanter in the group(even level 50 sltw is 60%+40% epic=100%). <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/udropthe.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Dropthe</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/3/02 5:57:02 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousetrainingstudioqafornewbies.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=12350.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Haste cap</span><hr size=1> Don't know why, but for some reason I thought that this topic was about a cool new helmet with haste LOL. =P<br>
<br>
I don't know why I thought that, but its what popped into my mind when I saw the title.<br>
<br>
BTW: I'd like to hear the answer to this also. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ugyorg.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Gyorg</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_fire.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Moderator</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/3/02 6:32:25 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousetrainingstudioqafornewbies.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=12350.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.mines.edu/students/g/gbassett/orion.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Haste cap</span><hr size=1> I remember someone did the tests and basically they came out inconclusive as to whether the 51+ haste cap was 100 or 105.  There was some specific reason but I cannot remember what it was.  It was concluded though that RB+any post-50 chanter haste hit the haste cap.<br>
<br>
As for pre-50, I don't believe anyone has run tests to determine it in the recent past. <p>--------------------------
